## Postman Collection

Import this into Postman for easy testing:

1. Create a new collection "E-Learning API"
2. Add environment variables:
   - `baseUrl`: https://localhost:5001
   - `userToken`: (set after login)
   - `adminToken`: (set after admin login)
3. Add all the above requests
4. Use `{{baseUrl}}` and `{{userToken}}` placeholders

### Testing File Upload in Postman:
1. Set request method to POST
2. Set URL: {{baseUrl}}/api/manualpayment
3. Headers: Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
4. Body tab → select "form-data"
5. Add fields:
   - ContentId: 1 (Text)
   - TransferMethod: 1 (Text)
   - ReferenceNumber: IP123456 (Text)
   - Screenshot: [Select File]

